keyFacts: The document is a comprehensive travel log for Jeffrey Epstein generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on June 25, 2019, covering movements from 2015 to 2017.
Epstein traveled extensively using private aircraft with tail numbers N212JE, N415LM, N331JE, and N908JE, indicating access to multiple private planes.
Travel patterns show frequent flights between the New York/New Jersey area (TEB, ISP, JFK, EWR), Florida (PBI), and the Caribbean (STT, EIS, PAP), with occasional trips to Europe (CDG, IST).
Many entries show "Name No Name, No APIS" for fellow passengers, indicating the flight manifests did not include Advanced Passenger Information System data for other travelers.
The document includes both air travel records and vehicle border crossings (noted as "VEHICLE"), suggesting Epstein also crossed US borders by car.
